<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Career Guidance - Web Development</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        header {
            background-color: #0077cc;
            color: white;
            padding: 20px 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
        section {
            background-color: white;
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #0077cc;
        }
        ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }
        footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 40px;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: gray;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Career Guidance in Web Development</h1>
        <p>Your journey to becoming a web developer starts here!</p>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Why Choose Web Development?</h2>
        <p>Web development is a growing field with many opportunities. It offers creative freedom, remote working options, and strong salary prospects.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Skills You Need</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>HTML, CSS, and JavaScript fundamentals</li>
            <li>Responsive Design (Mobile-first approach)</li>
            <li>Front-end Frameworks (e.g., React, Vue.js)</li>
            <li>Back-end Development (e.g., Node.js, PHP)</li>
            <li>Databases (SQL, MongoDB)</li>
            <li>Version Control (Git/GitHub)</li>
            <li>Problem-solving and continuous learning</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Career Paths</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Front-end Developer</li>
            <li>Back-end Developer</li>
            <li>Full-stack Developer</li>
            <li>UI/UX Designer</li>
            <li>Web Designer</li>
            <li>DevOps Engineer</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Resources to Get Started</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>FreeCodeCamp.org</li>
            <li>MDN Web Docs (by Mozilla)</li>
            <li>W3Schools</li>
            <li>Coursera Web Development Courses</li>
            <li>GitHub for hosting your projects</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

